                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 <persName corresp="#p_WRACH1"
                        >Woodward</persName> Electoral Mission/124: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-16T16:00:00-05:45"
                            >July 16, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>129. Legation’s telegram 124, July 15, 9 a.m. Contract for sale of gasoline
                    storage tank in Corinto to West India Oil Company was approved by Congress
                    yesterday. Balance of sale price, approximately $10,000, will probably be paid
                    to Government sometime next week. I intend to discuss with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJM2">Moncada</persName> tomorrow the possibility of securing
                    from this source additional funds urgently needed by the Electoral Mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HME1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
